# Online Learning System

A lightweight online learning platform for creating courses, lessons, quizzes, and tracking student progress.

Features
- User roles: admin, instructor, student
- Course and lesson management
- Quizzes and basic auto-grading
- Progress tracking and simple analytics
- File/video attachments and rich text content

Tech stack
- Backend: (e.g., Node.js / Django — replace with actual)
- Frontend: (e.g., React / Vue)
- Database: PostgreSQL / MySQL
- Authentication: JWT (or replace as used)

Quickstart (local)
1. Clone repository
   git clone https://github.com/longchanreaksa/online-learning-system.git
   cd online-learning-system
2. Install dependencies
   # example for Node
   npm install
3. Create environment file
   cp .env.example .env
   # set DATABASE_URL, JWT_SECRET, PORT, etc.
4. Database
   # create DB and run migrations (example)
   createdb online_learning
   npm run migrate
5. Run
   npm run dev
   Open http://localhost:3000

Environment (example)
- DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:pass@localhost:5432/online_learning
- JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret
- PORT=3000

Testing
- Run unit and integration tests:
  npm test

Docker (optional)
- Build and start:
  docker-compose up --build
- Ensure env vars are set in docker-compose or .env

Deployment notes
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Use managed DB (RDS / Cloud SQL) and object storage (S3)
- Serve static assets via CDN in production

Project layout (high level)
- /backend - API and server code
- /frontend - client app
- /docs - design & screenshots
- /migrations - DB migrations
- docker-compose.yml, Dockerfile, README.md

Contributing
1. Fork the repo
2. Create a branch: git checkout -b feat/your-feature
3. Commit, push, and open a PR
Please include tests and update docs for major changes.

